Abstract;
The main objective of this research work is to preserve and conserve the original Palm leaves manuscripts by few scientific experimental lab work. As we know Environmental factors plays a major role in preserving any kind of Manuscripts. In this aspects, we have chosen to study the role of environmental factors on palm leaves manuscripts. We have selected different Manuscript library regions which has different climatic condition.  The Plate exposure method, also known as the settle plate method or passive air sampling method here allows physical settling of airborne microorganisms onto the surface of Nutrient agar (Bacteria) and Potato Dextrose agar (Fungi) petri plate. Once on the agar plate, where nutrient and moisture content will be there allowing microorganisms to grow and multiply, forming visible colonies. Further identification of microorganisms will be carried out with specific staining techniques in vitro. 
Key Words; Nutrient agar, Potato Dextrose agar, Petri plates, Microorganisms.
